   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SUPPLYING CLEAN WATER TO THE ORPHANAGE -  SCHOOL</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Having access to adequate sanitation is the only way that would help reduce illness and deaths of young children and people caused by drinking unclean water, from different sources, located nearby or far away of the Orphanage and Iwacu Kazoza School. A  Well has been drilled and Water has been found; it is pure and plenty of water. The remaining work to be done is to install water solar pump, pipes, build water tanks then to supply water  to the school, orphanage and surrounding community.</narrative>
  </description>
